# CCNA Study Reference: The OSI 7-Layer Model

This document serves as a structured reference guide for the **Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) Reference Model**, specifically tailored for CCNA preparation and network troubleshooting fundamentals. Understanding the precise functions, Protocol Data Units (PDUs), and associated devices of each layer is essential for mastering Cisco architectures.

---

## 1. The OSI Model Architecture at a Glance

Data moving down the stack (Layers 7 to 1) undergoes **Encapsulation** (adding headers/trailers), while data moving up the stack (Layers 1 to 7) undergoes **Decapsulation** (stripping headers).

| Layer | Layer Name | PDU (Data Unit) | Primary Responsibility | Key Protocols & Hardware |
| :---: | :--- | :---: | :--- | :--- |
| **7** | **Application** | Data | Network services directly to end-user applications. | HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, DNS, DHCP |
| **6** | **Presentation**| Data | Data formatting, encryption, and compression. | SSL/TLS, JPEG, ASCII, MPEG |
| **5** | **Session** | Data | Establishes, manages, and terminates sessions. | NetBIOS, RPC, Sockets |
| **4** | **Transport** | **Segment** | End-to-end reliable delivery, flow control, port addressing. | **TCP, UDP** / L4 Switches |
| **3** | **Network** | **Packet** | Logical addressing (IP) and path determination (Routing). | **IPv4, IPv6**, ICMP, OSPF / **Router**, L3 Switch |
| **2** | **Data Link** | **Frame** | Physical addressing (MAC) and hop-to-hop data transfer. | **Ethernet**, ARP, VLAN / **Switch**, Bridge |
| **1** | **Physical** | **Bit** | Transmission of raw unstructured bitstreams over media. | Cables (UTP, Fiber), RJ-45 / Hub, Repeater |

